<div id="map_canvas" style="width:100%; height:100%"></div>

<a href="http://www.unep-wcmc.org" target="_blank" id="logo"></a>

<div id="map_menu" >
  <div id='layers-box' class='well'>
    <div class='control-row'>
      <div class="btn-group layer-switcher layers" data-toggle="buttons-radio">
        <button class="show-mangroves btn btn-warning active" title="Show mangroves layer">Mangroves</button>
        <button class="show-corals btn" title="Show corals layer">Corals</button>
      </div>
      <a href="#" class="hide-data-layers btn" data-toggle="button" title="Hide layers"><i class="icon-eye-close"></i></a>
    </div>

    <div class='control-row'>
      <div class="btn-group layer-switcher " data-toggle="buttons-radio">
        <button class="use-satellite btn btn-info active" title="Use satellite base layer">Satellite</button>
        <button class="use-terrain btn" title="Use terrain base layer">Terrain</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='control-row break'>
      <div class="btn-group zoom-group">
        <a href="#" class="zoom-in btn" title="Zoom in"><i class="icon-plus"></i></a>
        <a href="#" class="zoom-out btn" title="Zoom out"><i class="icon-minus"></i></a>
      </div>
      <a href="#" class="help btn btn-info"><i class="icon-question-sign icon-white"></i></a>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<div id="main_menu">
  <div class="actions hide">
    <div class="btn-group">
      <a class="edit-area btn btn-warning dropdown-toggle" data-toggle="dropdown" href="#"><i class="icon-pencil icon-white"></i> Edit area <span class="caret"></span></a>
      <ul class="dropdown-menu">
        <li><a href="#" class="add-area"><i class="icon-plus"></i> Add new area</a></li>
        <li><a href="#" class="delete-area"><i class="icon-trash"></i> Delete area</a></li>
        <li class="divider hide"></li>
        <li class="hide"><a href="#" class="cancel-edit-area">Cancel</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <a href="#" class="validate btn btn-primary" data-toggle="button"><i class="icon-ok icon-white"></i> Validate area</a>
    <div class="submit-or-erase btn-group hide">
      <a href="#" class="submit-polygon btn btn-inverse disabled"><i class="icon-check icon-white"></i> Submit</a>
      <a href="#" class="erase-polygon btn btn-danger disabled"><i class="icon-repeat icon-white"></i> Erase</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <a href="#" class="select-layer btn btn-inverse hide disabled">Select a layer to continue editing</a>
  <a href="#" class="zoom btn btn-inverse">Zoom in to region to start editing</a>
</div>

<!-- Modals -->
<div class="modal" id="landingModal">
  <div class="modal-header">
    <a class="close" data-dismiss="modal">×</a>
    <h3>Mangrove and Coral Editing and Validation Tool</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="modal-body">
    <div class="logos">
      <%= link_to image_tag('icri_logo.gif'), 'http://www.icriforum.org/' %>
      <%= link_to image_tag('usdos_seal_logo.png'), 'http://www.state.gov/' %>
      <%= link_to image_tag('cclme.png'), 'http://www.canarycurrent.org/' %>
      <%= link_to image_tag('unep_wcmc_logo.png'), 'http://unep-wcmc.org/' %>
    </div>
    <p>This portal is designed to allow basic editing and validation of the Global Distribution of Coral Reefs (2010) and the African subset of the USGS Global Distribution of Mangrove (2000) datasets held by UNEP-WCMC. This is a beta version with limited functionality as yet but allows users to edit the spatial data and/or validate the datasets based on:</p>
    <ol class="letters">
      <li>Local knowledge of the habitat in question</li>
      <li>Obvious omission/commission errors in the data</li>
      <li>Basic user interpretation of the underlying imagery</li>
    </ol>
    <p>The outcome of this input will be more reliable African mangrove and coral reef habitat spatial data through increased data validation and verification.</p>
    <p>Simply choose the dataset you wish to edit and zoom in to the desired area. Select the type of editing that you want to undertake: Validate (agree with existing areas), Add or Delete, using the tool bar on the top right of the screen, and then start editing.</p>
    <h3>Editing limitations</h3>
    <p>The temporal resolution of the edited Coral reef and Mangrove datasets will difficult to define as they will combine the temporal range of the baseline dataset and the added edits of the user community.</p>
    <p>All edits should be based on clear errors/omissions in the data. Where there is any ambiguity, no edits/additions should be made. e.g. mangrove forests and terrestrial forest cover can be very hard to distinguish without viewing the region in a satellite image band combination suitable for mangrove identification, so it is not expected that users would undertake any differentiation between these two habitat types unless they had in-depth local knowledge.</p>
    <p>Future functionalities will allow users to:</p>
    <ol class="roman">
      <li>Specify the type of editing they have undertaken (e.g. a, b or c above).</li>
      <li>Upload their own spatial data for integration into the community dataset.</li>
      <li>Download subsets of the dataset according to their own defined area of interest.</li>
      <li>View imagery with explicit dates to facilitate local habitat change detection analyses.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>For any feedback or questions, please email <%= mail_to "niall.phelan@unep-wcmc.org" %>.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="modal-footer">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal">Get started</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="modal hide" id="submitModal">
  <div class="modal-header">
    <a class="close" data-dismiss="modal">×</a>
    <h3>Mangrove and Coral Validation Tool</h3>
  </div>
  <%= render 'form' %>
</div>
